{
  "id": "nce2-l92",
  "title": "Lesson 92: Asking for Trouble",
  "audio": "/audio/nce2/92ÔºçAsking for Trouble.mp3",
  "image": "/images/coming-soon.png",
  "segments": [
    {
      "id": "intro_1",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "Why did the policeman ask the writer to come to the police station?",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 10.4,
      "endTime": 17.4
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_2",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "It must have been about two in the morning when I returned home.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 17.41,
      "endTime": 22.76
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_3",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "I tried to wake up my wife by ringing the doorbell,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 22.77,
      "endTime": 26.82
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_4",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "but she was fast asleep,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 26.83,
      "endTime": 29.24
    },
    {
      "id": "s1",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "so I got a ladder from the shed in the garden, put it against the wall,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 29.25,
      "endTime": 34.7
    },
    {
      "id": "s2",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "and began climbing towards the bedroom window.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 34.71,
      "endTime": 38.59
    },
    {
      "id": "s3",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "I was almost there when a sarcastic voice below said.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 38.6,
      "endTime": 44.35
    },
    {
      "id": "s4",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "'I don't think the windows need cleaning at this time of the night.'",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 44.36,
      "endTime": 50.06
    },
    {
      "id": "s5",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "I looked down and nearly fell off the ladder when I saw a policeman.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 50.07,
      "endTime": 56.44
    },
    {
      "id": "s6",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "I immediately regretted answering in the way I did, but I said, 'I enjoy cleaning windows at night.'",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 56.45,
      "endTime": 67.85
    },
    {
      "id": "s7",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "'So do I,' answered the policeman in the same tone.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 67.86,
      "endTime": 73.35
    },
    {
      "id": "s8",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "Excuse my interrupting you.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 73.36,
      "endTime": 76.19
    },
    {
      "id": "s9",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "I hate to interrupt a man when he's busy working, but would you mind coming with me to the station?'",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 76.2,
      "endTime": 85.81
    },
    {
      "id": "s10",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "'Well, I'd prefer to stay here,' I said.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 85.82,
      "endTime": 90.63
    },
    {
      "id": "s11",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "'You see, I've forgotten my key.'",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 90.64,
      "endTime": 94.11
    },
    {
      "id": "s12",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "'Your what?' he called.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 94.12,
      "endTime": 97.1
    },
    {
      "id": "s13",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "'My key,' I shouted.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 97.11,
      "endTime": 101.2
    },
    {
      "id": "s14",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "Fortunately, the shouting woke up my wife who opened the window just as the policeman had started to climb towards me.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 101.21,
      "endTime": 106.21
    }
  ]
}